</td></tr></table>
		<br>
	<img src="http://www.eqcleric.com/images/awards/claviger.png" alt="Claviger of Lore"><br><a href="/show.php?pg=Donation"><img src="/images/supporter.gif" border="0" width="60" height="60"></a>	</td></tr></table>
	<!-- Postbit User Info -->
</td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#666699" width="100%" valign="top">
	
	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 06-19-2004 <font color="#FEDE01">11:05 PM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">As some of you may know, there's a lengthy series of discussions going on at the moment between the priest classes.  Basically, some priests (particularly shamans) have expressed the concern that they're basically useless in GoD and they want large healing upgrades to give themselves something useful to do - so the discussion is about rebalancing the priest classes with that in mind.<br />
<br />
Now, to me, it's a no-brainer that if you implement large increases to druid and shaman healing, you'd need to alter clerics quite a bit to compensate.<br />
<br />
There's a fairly large contingent of clerics who don't <i>want</i> priest class rebalancing, of course.  I understand that view - but I also believe that's probably shortsighted.  History teaches us that where druids and shamans ask for large healing upgrades, there's a fair chance that they'll get them.  And some recent comments by Rytan the Wyrmlord (who's the EQ "Spell Guy", if you didn't know, although he prefers to be called Ryan) suggest that he's at least considering the idea.<br />
<br />
This time, I don't intend for clerics to be caught on the hop.  This time, I want a clear consensus from the cleric community about how we'd want clerics to be upgraded when and if healing upgrades for druids and shamans are implemented.<br />
<br />
The discussion's taking place on the Priest's Covenant, and it's being hosted by Sobe Silvertree on the Druid's Grove.  There are three cleric "Guardians" (which means "cleric advocate, representative, and moderator") there, and I'm enormously proud to say that the DG has given me the chance to be one of them.<br />
<br />
So, following an initial round of discussions on the Priest's Covenant, and after collecting ideas from talking to an awful lot of clerics, here's the current list of balancing ideas for clerics!<br />
<br />
Comments are invited.  <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="Smile"><br />
 __________________________________________________<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Note:</b> This is a long list! I'm not suggesting that all of these ideas should necessarily be implemented. I'm mentioning them for consideration by the cleric community, and I expect at least some of them to be rejected.<br />
<br />
In suggesting this list, I've assumed that druids and shamans become viable main healers for exp groups up to and including mid-range GoD content (say, as far as Kod Taz.)<br />
<br />
I can't take credit for all these ideas! They're mostly a compilation of ideas originally submitted by other people, some of which were expanded by me, with a couple of my own thoughts chucked in.  I'm particularly grateful to Nosmok Ing for the suggestion of clerical hymns.<br />
<br />
<b>Melee: Offensive</b><br />
<br />
<b>Objective:</b> To fix the cleric melee implemented in 2002 which is presently in the same state as it was in early PoP and has been ignored since. <br />
<ul><br />
<li>Increase weapon skill caps to 200 in line with shamans <br />
<li>Enable purchase of double attack skill (possibly via AA) <br />
<li>Enable purchase of melee damage table (possibly via AA) (capped so a level 70 cleric melees like a level 55 paladin) <br />
<li>Enable purchase of the Weapon Affinity AA <br />
<li>Increase choice of weapons (probably by adding the Hand of the Gods proc as a LDON-purchasable type 4 augment)* <br />
</ul><br />
* Issue: How to prevent people from augmenting an existing Hand of the Gods proccing weapon with a second HoTG proc? <br />
<br />
<b>Melee: Defensive</b><br />
<br />
<b>Objective:</b> To increase cleric survivability under attack to a level more appropriate to a plate class. <br />
<ul><br />
<li>Increase dodge cap to 125 <br />
<li>Enable purchase of parry and riposte skills to 75 and 50 respectively <br />
<li>Implement an improved version of Vie which would be self-only <br />
<li>Allow AotZ to stack with Focus as AotC does <br />
</ul><br />
<b>Nuke DPS</b><br />
<br />
<b>Objective:</b> To increase cleric nuke DPS so it becomes closer to, but still less efficient and powerful than, druid nuke DPS <br />
<ul><br />
<li>Remove pushback component from cleric live-target nukes <br />
<li>Add the option of a different resist check (possibly fire-based nukes) <br />
<li>Reduce recast delay on live-target nukes <br />
</ul><br />
<b>Crowd Control/Pulling</b><br />
<br />
<b>Objective:</b> To expand the cleric's existing capabilities in this area, while ensuring that clerics do not overtake bards/enchanters <br />
<ul><br />
<li>Increase the duration of Pacification and the new OoW spell Placate <br />
<li>Fix Atone so that it has a reasonable chance of working <br />
<li>Add a success/fail message to Atone <br />
<li>Consider implementing "Hymns" referred to below <br />
</ul><br />
<b>General</b><br />
<br />
<b>Objective:</b> To remove the unfair and unreasonable peridot cost imposed on clerics. Also, to give clerics invis. There's some other general purpose utility shared by the other casters on this list as well, but this is basically about invis. Also, I wish to stress that in my opinion, clerics should be able to cast invis.  *grins*<br />
<ul><br />
<li>Enable clerics to cast Invis, possibly via a hymn (see below) <br />
<li>Enable clerics to cast Enduring Breath, See Invis, and Levitate, possibly via hymns (see below) <br />
<li>Remove the unfair and unreasonable peridot cost from all clerical hp buffs. <br />
</ul><br />
<b>Hymns</b><br />
<br />
Put very simply, in this model hymns would be the clerical answer to bard songs. The same code as bard songs could be used. Note that clerics wouldn't be able to use instruments, although the "Singing" skill could be added for clerics, capped lower than for bards, and hymns would be affected by singing mods. <br />
<br />
Hymns would be implemented for: <br />
<ul><br />
<li>A short-duration mezz hymn equivalent to bardic mezz <br />
<li>A tash hymn equivalent to the bardic resist debuffer <br />
<li>A self-invis hymn <br />
<li>A "faerune" hymn which combines ultravision, see invis, and eb <br />
<li>A levitating hymn <br />
</ul></font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
	</td></tr></table>
	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	</td>
