	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Agree with most of what was said above.  Two things if they had to go again would be Offensive abilites and Nuke DPS.   <br />
<br />
However i would suggest that the cleric class does NOT get Riposte, we are not melee or a hybrid class, let them keep at least some sort of defensive ability.  Instead maybe institute a ability called blocking which works only when a shield is equipped (available to all classes) and have this instead of the riposte.  Increasing our Dodge cap though is a must.  Allowing AotZ to stack with focus i think is another big one,  IMHO its unfair that a Paladin gets a self buff almost the same as the cleric's self buff (5 more HP, 3 more AC, but only 4 Mana per tick regen) but that it is able to stack with the Fo7 line.<br />
<br />
Concerning the complete abolishment of peridots i disagree somewhat.  I agree that the peridots have to go from all our HP buffs but i do feel that the cleric HP should have a component required to cast it.  Something like carnelian, onyx, or lapis lazulis all of which cost less than a plat.<br />
<br />
The success/failure message on atone is another big one imho, currently clerics have no way of clearing agro apart from zoning.  Most other classes have at least some way to lose agro or have a decent pet to take the agro off them: Monks, SK's, Necro: FD, Rogues: Escape, Druid, Wizzy: Succor, ect.  With at least a message on atone to let us know if it worked would be really helpful.<br />
<br />
Hymns are by far one of the best ideas ive heard so far, personally i love that idea.  However i think it would be nice if SoE gave us an extra 2 spell slots usable ONLY for Hymn spells since we would be the only class which has both Song type and Spell type "spells".  Also one concern that i think would need to be addressed with the hymns is casting a spell while "singing a hymn", would we have to stop our hymn to cast a spell and if so how long would the effects of the hymn last after we stopped? Once that small concern is addressed i feel this could be the best idea to hit clerics in a LONG while.<br />
<br />
Just out of curiosity who are the other two cleric reps?</font></p>
	
	<p><p><img src="/forums/images/sig_separator.gif" width="282" height="11" Alt="Hey! Watch where you point that thing!"><br>
<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">

Aondail Shadowbane<br />
65th Season Cleric of Drinal<br />
