	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">I like the idea of the defense modifications. Even the offense sounds alright to me [although the Weapon Affinity seems rather... uneven]. <br />
<br />
Perhaps I will be ripped apart for this, but this is distressing to me. A cleric's job is to <b>heal</b>, no? Does it not make sense that our heals should be superior to other priests? Once we get mezzing and debuffs from our hymns, what'll we do to/for the enchanters and bards to compensate for us receiving that ability?<br />
<br />
What I'm getting at is our job is to <b>heal</b>. We are not paladins, we are not wizards, we are not bards, we are <b>clerics</b>.<br />
<br />
<b>Edit:</b> What about lifting the Complete Heal limit so it's... actually a complete heal again? Or maybe an overflow where if you over heal someone, the remaining hp flows into the rest of the group.</font></p>
	
