	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">I definitly like Melee Offensive, and most of Melee Defensive(also feel riposte is unnecessary) but I'm not sure about the other two.  Rytan has already said in the Enchanter Q & A that they are considering throwing in a nuke that has a worse mana to damage ratio but a different resist type, this should be the same for us since we also have a one resists nuke selection.  But don't increase our nukes, our job is damage mitigation, if beefing up druids and shamans is to happen the last thing I want them to do is make clerics more wizardly.  As for hymns, I personally have an enchanter and no no no, Enchanters already hate it enough that bards have been and are getting beefed up, we don't need Clerical Enchanters, uber healing powers and ability to save the day with mez.  Its not that our job would be so much as taken, but instead groups will be thinking, Enchanter or *non enchanter class here*, well we could use some DPS and cleric can handle bad pulls =/  As for tash, I don't think its needed, especially since Rytan doesn't want to beef up Tash that is significantly weaker than its shaman/mage counterparts but generates more aggro.  (they are going to tweak aggro however).  But I DO like the invis, lev and EB idea, ( but can you hum (hymn hum hehe i know smart) invis while have invis vs ud on you?) whether it is hymns or spells.  If they do make it hymns there should be more hymns than just these three, maybe a group Divine Intervention hymn similar to the bards in every (forget how often) a tiny Rune is replenished, (bards has a 50 one, not sure if its continued beyond that) or possibly a group life regen spell, or a single target regen spell that focuses the healing as to make them regen MUCH faster than nomal and a good deal faster than with just normal regen hymn, and these should all be manaless like bards.  And maybe one that increases resists also? ooo oooo one that increases a resist depending on Diety? I dont know I love the idea of diety specific spell. Thats something they shoudl think about if there adding new spells.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
