	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><table border="0" align="center" width="90%" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1"><tr><td><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><b>quote:</b></font></td></tr><tr><td style="BORDER: #000000 1px solid; FONT-SIZE: 11px; COLOR: #FFFFFF; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana,Arial; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #4D4D73;">Mayliu said in post <a href="http://www.eqcleric.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&postid=#post" target="_blank">#8 </a>:<br />
<b>I have no desire to be a mezzer.<br />
I have no desire to be a debuffer.<br />
<br />
What I do want..<br />
To stay and remain the strongest healer in the game.<br />
To have a better ability to solo.<br />
<br />
Unlike other utility classes, our job is clear and specific...to heal.  Shaman and Druids have other utility spells because their job is slightly less specific.   I can't see them giving us all of what you've mentioned without the EQ community crying out that we are way overpowered and then (at least in my opinion) other classes would be screaming for balancing.<br />
<br />
 </b></td></tr></table> <br />
<br />
I totaly agree with Mayliu.  We are not mezzers, debuffers ect.  We are not paladins! Our role in a group will never be dps or crowd control.  Our job is ... to HEAL!  I can care less about how much malee damage I can do.  I do care however about not taking "the strongest healer in game" away from us.  <br />
<br />
Sure there is room for improvement in a few areas but the promiss to fix those in exchange to making our position in the game much weaker is a bad trade off IMO.  I can pay for my peridots (have been for years); I can deal with not having invis.. we all do.. I can use Pacify even as it is with competence...sure I would like my armor to reflect being a plate class little more but the price for it is too high the way it is proposed.  <br />
<br />
Shaman can slow.. that is a Huge utility in itself.. there is no group without a slower.  Not to mention the great buffs shamans get and their great benefit and usefulness to any group (those are not buffs you can always do without).  To make a shaman heal as good as Cleric does not seem "balanced" to me at all.  I wonder why shaman would not ask to be a better CC (have mez) since it already has a slow (like enchanter) and a very reliable root AA.  Hmm that would not make enchanters happy would it? How is that we should be happy with making them better healers?  I do not see those changes as balancing.. I see them as debalancing.<br />
<br />
Druids have snare, port, debuffs, better nucks, they can SOLO effectively and they are very close to us in healing as it is (at least in my guild they are very active paticipants in healing groups and as a part of CH rotations).  The only thing that truly separates us from Druids as healers is their lack of Rez.  <br />
<br />
If they are going to make those two classes better healers (and there is no way arround it) they should make us better Clerics (not paladins or enchanters ect).  How about MGB rez AA?  How about self rez AA for us with 100% mana restored (and I mean full mana after you put your armor on not before) and no exp loss?  How about making our plate armor mean something because it should have been done long time ago?  How about AA that would increase our casting level enough to elminate fizzles all together?  How about making CH a true CH and allowing fucus effects to modify it (aside from ER)?  <br />
<br />
The problem does not lie in balancing the classes.   The idea was to make us all unique and not "alike" in utility.  The problem lies in a bad game design where the utilities of other classes are not being made as important.  IF we all are going to be able to do anything another class does with similar competency.. what is the difference which class we pick?  Maybe we should all play just one class.. and asign "jobs" each person does in group ourselves....that would make getting groups easy for sure&gt;&lt;.<br />
<br />
Bleh.. to that whole idea!<br />
<br />
Nellai TheFaithful<br />
Archon of the 7th Hammer<br />
The Raging Tide</font></p>
	
