	<td bgcolor="#666699" width="100%" valign="top">
	
	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 06-20-2004 <font color="#FEDE01">06:42 PM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Heya,<br />
<br />
     I like the idea behind upping our offensive melee as far as adding Hand of the Gods augments, but dont see a need for clerics to have double attack...that should be reserved for actual melee classes imo.  Oh, and as far as fixing it so that you cant proc twice i dont really see *that much* of a problem considering you can currently add a liftap augment to cleric usable hammers with the Hand of the Gods proc already (Hammer of Zek, Hammer of Hours, etc). Offensive nuke upgrades should be limited to only providing more than one type of nuke as well (fire/cold/magic), there's not that much good reason to give us *huge* nuke upgrades damage wise.  This is especially true when things about the cleric class that are already there that could be fixed alone would  help immensely such as fixing the TU AA ability, our undead dot efficiency , and perhaps more viable upgrades to our Damage shields.  I would like to see something similar to the "cleric mezz" idea as well , but not really as a mezz. Think Necromancer "Screaming Terror"...in other words it would actually just be a longer duration stun and not so much of a mezz (but code it as a mezz so that mobs that are normally un-mezzable/un-stunnable remain s<img src="images/smilies/alien.gif" border="0" alt="Alien">.<br />
<br />
     Defensively we definately need work. You know when i do GoD raids and such (ikk3-4 atm) I dont even bother asking for HP rebuffs?  There's no point since i die in one round, so instead i focus soley on mana regen really.  From what i've read AC for clerics does work exactly the same as AC for other plate classes, but what is making the difference outside of AA's/discs is that we have no avoidance. We cant dodge a blow for snot =P. That is what makes us crumple like a paper sack i think (feel free to correct me if i'm wrong here btw, i'm just typing things as they come to mind).  So along with some decent avoidance i think that parry is a great idea, but shoudn't be used mid-cast because that would make no sense O_o.  I dont like the idea of cleric riposte though as that's taking it a bit too far into stepping into melee classes' realm.  So far though concerning the melee standpoint i do agree with everything listed in Shadowfrost's post except for those things i've mentioned so far.<br />
<br />
     With the "Crowd Control/Pulling" section, i really really really *Love* the idea of a success/fail message for atone, and/or possibly an upgrade. I dont see much point in upping our paci skill so much though if they stay in the same basic range that they've always been, meaning "doable, but not neccesarily as good as an enchanter's". We have Enchanters, bards, monks, and SK's who can pull most anything well, and that's not including clerics....we're ok in comparison to other classes concerning pulling alone i think. I *do not* like the idea of having a bard-like mezz though, hymn or not.  We're better of having something more of a long duration stun so as not to spread ourselves out like that.  Besides, stuns stay well within the realm of cleric'ing..and i have no wish to begin "twisting hymns" especially when i'm spam healing/Chain CH'ing in a nasty spot =P.<br />
<br />
     Please, please, please get rid of the peridot cost for HP buffs...or at least do something with them so that clerics dont have to be broke all the time =/.  We can't solo farm (very well at all at least), many of us end up eating the cost of the reagents alot of times if we're not group leader and not assigned ML.  I ended up making a necromancer (which i  love dearly~) so that i could finally farm for myself and not have to get help killing things =/.  If the reagent cost cannot be removed, either make our HP buffs work with less-expensive reagents or perhaps just less reagents O_o.  I dont know if it would be at all possible but one idea would be to have each peridot consist of "charges" per say, like a mana battery sort of.  Each dot could be two or three charges of HP buffs or something /shrug (i'm grasping here because before i joined my current guild which supplies our cleric's with dots i stayed broke my entire cleric career between having to buy spells, armor upgrades, peridots etc).<br />
<br />
     I like the idea of hymns...it's something new and fun from the sound of it =D.  I do have concerns though.  If they are going to be "bard-like songs"  will we have to twist them? I dont know about you guys but trying to keep the timing on those while also tryin to heal a group/raid (we spend alot of time smacking those heal keys =D) sounds a little harsh O_o.  As stated before as well, I dont like the idea of having a bard-mezz, or the resist debuffer either.  That's too close to being a bard, and there are other classes that debuff that have enough problems of their own without clerics intruding into their area and making them feel even more unwanted. Ahhh, but hence comes the place from which our new-found utilities may arise~ =D. <br />
<br />
     I absolutely *Love* the idea for hymns that give us/our group Faerune, and lev..and for us the ever-coveted self invis. I wonder though if utilities like these would require us to not cast any other spells or else the hymn stops, guess that would be okay too though as these types of "spells" are more or less just a way to provide clerics with a more feasible means of travel other than waiting for our cloudy potion to stop working then root/paci/atone O_o. So Utility Hymns gets a BIG YES from me. However offensive/defensvie hymns would be going too far imo.<br />
<br />
     One last thought before i end the longest post i've ever made here (i'm more of a lurker LOL).  Something to keep in mind when seeking upgrades/balance to the priest classes is the parent/hybrid issue.  What ever you do to a parent class may cause that parent's "child" as it were to seek those same changes.  If that were to occur (i.e. Clerics get faerune hymns, so paladins wish to recieve a like ability or just hymns in general) imagine the uproar that could cuase for our opposites.  Clerics get hymns, so paladins want them too..and in time get some.  Shadowknights see this and scream "Hey! where's our upgrade???".  Then necros say "Well we are your parent class, so if you get upgraded, then we should get a more powerful form of your new ability".  The same things could be said for Shaman/Beastlord, Druid/Ranger.....sorry if i seem to be dragging up alot of stuff that no one really wants to think about, but it seems that since SoE dosent think very well for itself it becomes our job to think for them if we wish this game to remain enjoyable for everyone =).  Yes, i know i'm jumping the gun by a long shot by even thinking that stuff, but considering how much i like strategy...it kinda comes naturally to think ahead and consider all possibilites =D.<br />
<br />
     So there ya go, my longest post here....and now i need more tea O_o.  I would just like to say Thank you Shadowfrost for stepping up to the plate to help represent the cleric class, we all do very much appreciate the time and effort you are putting in to do so (as well as the other cleric represenatives), and also thank you for posting and giving us the opportunity to state our wishes/comments and concerns. /Salute Shadowfrost /dance<br />
<br />
                                                                   Exarch Tyyora Sola<br />
                                                               The Royal Norrathian Guard<br />
                                                                      Tribunal Server<br />
<br />
P.S. sorry for any spelling/grammar errors, i just woke up from a long night =P</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
