	<td bgcolor="#666699" width="100%" valign="top">
	
	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 06-20-2004 <font color="#FEDE01">07:50 PM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Having not gotten my cleric into the upper tier i can say nothing about that. Being a lvl 42 i can give my views on the shaman and druid reflection at this level. Personally i have played both a shaman and druid up into the mid 30s and saw that the two are extremly effective at this point. The cleric starts to shine once they get Sp. Heal before the rest but still druids and shamans can casst G.Heal which is only about 200 worst which isnt too bad at all. <br />
<br />
Another difference is the spells at hand. Clerics get their buffs true but a druid and shaman can give a group tons of buffs then heal almost as well as we can do on top of that. If you plan on improving the healing ability of the two thers then give us clerics some spells that make us more usefull at these levels, example: mabey a form of sow or some form that adds mana regan or something? Improving druids and shamans will not only affect how it works higher up but will also effect us lower lvls from getting group since all they have to do is get Temp to get all the buffs we can offer at that lvl.<br />
<br />
Overall i feel that improving the healing abiltiy of the others classes is a mistake because this will lower a clerics need at lower lvls causing less people to want to play the class. Also as clerics we are forced to group always pretty much. Not that i dont like this, its why i chose the class but druids and shamans have the option to solo so if they do improve the shamans and druids at least make it so that we can solo something besides undead. Well im done complaing Thanks all for reading<br />
Eanlaan</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><i>Last edited by Eanlaan on 06-20-2004 at 07:53 PM</i></font></p>
	</td></tr></table>
	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	</td>
</tr>
